Corral , in which the Earps and Holliday killed three of the Cowboys .', 'Pursuing a vendetta , Wyatt , his brother Warren , Holliday , and others formed a federal posse that killed three of the Cowboys whom they thought responsible .', 'Earp was a lifelong gambler and was always looking for a quick way to make money .', 'After leaving Tombstone , Earp went to San Francisco where he reunited with Josephine Earp .', 'They left there to race horses and open a saloon during a real estate boom in San Diego , California .', 'Back in San Francisco , Wyatt raced horses again , but his reputation suffered irreparably when he refereed the Fitzsimmons-Sharkey boxing match and called a foul that led many to believe that he fixed the fight .', 'In about 1911 , Earp began working several mining claims in Vidal , California , retiring in the hot summers with Josephine to Los Angeles .', 'He was known as a Western lawman , gunfighter , and boxing referee .', 'It became a bestseller and created his reputation as a fearless lawman .', "Earp 's modern-day reputation is that of the Old West 's `` toughest and deadliest gunman of his day .
